Current MRR classifier uses an LLM with PydanticOutputParser.
Same fragility as RMS — intermittent malformed JSON, hallucinated
personas, slow.

New approach: deterministic Python function that:
1. Normalizes the message (lowercase, strip punctuation).
2. Checks ordered list of keyword patterns per persona.
3. Returns a structured classification with HIGH confidence on match,
   LOW with fallback when no keywords match.

The Pydantic model returned must match what permission_check_node
currently consumes — so persona/collection/domain fields stay
identical.

